  "text": "Finally, firms seek ISO 9000 certification to realize efficiency gains. The discipline of documentation and organizational procedures could reduce waste, lower costs, and improve productivity. For example, relying on a survey of ISO 9000 certified firms in the U.S. (sales from $100 million to $500 million), [CITATION_1] report average annual savings of $200,000 due to the certification.",
